    18→ * <p>Typical interaction flow:
    19→ * <ol>
    20→ *     <li>Client creates a {@link PlaceOrderCommand} containing all information
    21→ *         necessary to attempt an order.</li>
    22→ *     <li>Domain service validates the command, performs credit-card authorization,
    23→ *         reserves inventory, and persists the {@code Order} aggregate.</li>
    24→ *     <li>A domain event <em>OrderPlaced</em> is published to notify interested
    25→ *         outbound adapters (email, webhooks, ERP sync, etc.).</li>
    26→ * </ol>
    27→ * </p>
