# Technical Plan: Warehouse Management System (WMS) Integration for SprintCart Pro

## Executive Summary

This document presents a detailed technical plan for integrating a third-party Warehouse Management System (WMS) into the SprintCart Pro e-commerce platform. The integration supports two critical business capabilities:

1. **Outbound Fulfillment Request**: When an order is successfully paid and confirmed, SprintCart Pro sends fulfillment details to the WMS API.
2. **Inbound Stock Update**: SprintCart Pro exposes a secure endpoint for the WMS to push real-time stock level updates.

This plan strictly adheres to the Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters) pattern established in ADR-001 and maintains consistency with existing C4 model documentation.

---

## 1. Module and Dependency Strategy

### 1.1 New Maven Module Required

A new adapter module should be created under the `sprintcart-pro-adapters` parent:

```
sprintcart-pro-adapters/
├── notification-adapter/
├── payment-adapter/
├── persistence-adapter/
├── search-adapter/
├── web-adapter/
└── wms-adapter/          <-- NEW MODULE
```

**Module Name:** `sprintcart-pro-adapters-wms`
**Artifact ID:** `wms-adapter`

### 1.2 Module Dependencies

#### New `wms-adapter` Module Dependencies

```xml
<dependencies>
    <!-- Internal Hexagonal Layers -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>com.sprintcart.pro</groupId>
        <artifactId>sprintcart-pro-domain</artifactId>
        <version>${project.version}</version>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>com.sprintcart.pro</groupId>
        <artifactId>sprintcart-pro-application</artifactId>
        <version>${project.version}</version>
    </dependency>

    <!-- HTTP Client for outbound WMS calls -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-webflux</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- REST endpoint for inbound WMS webhooks -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Security for webhook authentication -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Validation -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    <!-- Resilience patterns (circuit breaker, retry) -->
    <dependency>
        <groupId>io.github.resilience4j</groupId>
        <artifactId>resilience4j-spring-boot3</artifactId>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
```

#### Dependency Direction (Hexagonal Compliance)

Following the dependency rule from ADR-001 where "dependencies point inwards":

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      wms-adapter (new)                          │
│   ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│   │ WmsController (inbound REST)                             │  │
│   │ WmsRestClient (outbound HTTP)                            │  │
│   └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘  │
│                            │ depends on                         │
│   ┌────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────┐  │
│   │              sprintcart-pro-application                   │  │
│   │  (CatalogService, OrderService, DomainEventProcessor)     │  │
│   └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘  │
│                            │ depends on                         │
│   ┌────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────┐  │
│   │              sprintcart-pro-domain                        │  │
│   │  (WmsPort interfaces, domain events, value objects)       │  │
│   └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Key Constraint:** The `sprintcart-pro-domain` module must NOT depend on any adapter or framework-specific code.

---

## 2. Ports (Interfaces) Definition

Following the established pattern in the codebase (see `PaymentGatewayPort`, `ErpSystemPort`, `ManageCatalogUseCase`), we define both **outbound ports** and **inbound ports (use cases)**.

### 2.1 Outbound Port: `WmsPort` (Driven Port)

**Location:** `sprintcart-pro-domain/src/main/java/com/sprintcart/domain/ports/out/wms/WmsPort.java`

This port abstracts all outbound communication with the WMS. The domain layer calls this interface; the adapter implements it.

```java
package com.sprintcart.domain.ports.out.wms;

import java.time.Duration;
import java.time.Instant;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Objects;
import java.util.UUID;
import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;

/**
 * Outbound port that abstracts all interactions with an external Warehouse Management System (WMS).
 * <p>
 * Implementations reside in the infrastructure/adapter layer and handle protocol-specific
 * details (REST, webhooks, message queues). The domain layer depends solely on this interface,
 * ensuring complete decoupling from any particular WMS vendor or transport mechanism.
 *
 * <h3>Resilience</h3>
 * All operations return {@link CompletableFuture}s for non-blocking execution. Implementations
 * are expected to apply timeouts, retries, and circuit breaker patterns. Failures must be
 * propagated as {@link WmsIntegrationException}s.
 */
public interface WmsPort {

    /* ========================================================================
     * Fulfillment Operations (Outbound to WMS)
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Submits a fulfillment request to the WMS for processing.
     * <p>
     * This is typically called after an order is paid and ready for shipment.
     * The WMS will allocate inventory, generate picking lists, and coordinate
     * the physical fulfillment process.
     *
     * @param request Contains order details, shipping address, and line items.
     * @return Future containing the WMS acknowledgment with external reference.
     * @throws WmsIntegrationException if communication fails or WMS rejects the request.
     */
    CompletableFuture<FulfillmentAcknowledgment> submitFulfillmentRequest(FulfillmentRequest request)
            throws WmsIntegrationException;

    /**
     * Queries the current fulfillment status from the WMS.
     *
     * @param orderId SprintCart order identifier.
     * @return Future containing current status or empty if not found in WMS.
     */
    CompletableFuture<FulfillmentStatusResponse> getFulfillmentStatus(UUID orderId)
            throws WmsIntegrationException;

    /**
     * Cancels an in-progress fulfillment request.
     *
     * @param orderId SprintCart order identifier.
     * @param reason Cancellation reason for audit trail.
     * @return Future indicating success or failure.
     */
    CompletableFuture<Boolean> cancelFulfillment(UUID orderId, String reason)
            throws WmsIntegrationException;

    /* ========================================================================
     * Health & Diagnostics
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Performs a lightweight health check against the WMS endpoint.
     */
    WmsHealth healthCheck();

    /**
     * Returns WMS integration metadata for observability dashboards.
     */
    WmsMetadata metadata();

    /* ========================================================================
     * Value Objects & Records
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Request to initiate fulfillment for an order.
     */
    record FulfillmentRequest(
            UUID orderId,
            UUID customerId,
            String correlationId,
            ShippingDetails shippingDetails,
            List<FulfillmentLineItem> lineItems,
            FulfillmentPriority priority,
            Instant requestedAt
    ) {
        public FulfillmentRequest {
            Objects.requireNonNull(orderId, "orderId must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(customerId, "customerId must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(shippingDetails, "shippingDetails must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(lineItems, "lineItems must not be null");
            if (lineItems.isEmpty()) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("lineItems must not be empty");
            }
        }
    }

    /**
     * Individual line item within a fulfillment request.
     */
    record FulfillmentLineItem(
            UUID productId,
            String sku,
            String productName,
            int quantity,
            String specialInstructions
    ) {
        public FulfillmentLineItem {
            Objects.requireNonNull(productId, "productId must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(sku, "sku must not be null");
            if (quantity <= 0) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("quantity must be positive");
            }
        }
    }

    /**
     * Shipping destination details.
     */
    record ShippingDetails(
            String recipientName,
            String addressLine1,
            String addressLine2,
            String city,
            String state,
            String postalCode,
            String country,
            String phoneNumber,
            String shippingMethod
    ) {}

    /**
     * Priority level for fulfillment processing.
     */
    enum FulfillmentPriority {
        STANDARD,
        EXPRESS,
        SAME_DAY,
        PRIORITY
    }

    /**
     * Acknowledgment returned by WMS after accepting a fulfillment request.
     */
    record FulfillmentAcknowledgment(
            String wmsReferenceId,
            UUID orderId,
            FulfillmentStatus status,
            Instant acceptedAt,
            Instant estimatedShipDate
    ) {}

    /**
     * Current fulfillment status from WMS.
     */
    record FulfillmentStatusResponse(
            UUID orderId,
            String wmsReferenceId,
            FulfillmentStatus status,
            String trackingNumber,
            String carrier,
            Instant lastUpdated,
            List<FulfillmentEvent> events
    ) {}

    /**
     * Individual fulfillment milestone event.
     */
    record FulfillmentEvent(
            FulfillmentStatus status,
            String description,
            Instant occurredAt
    ) {}

    /**
     * Possible fulfillment states.
     */
    enum FulfillmentStatus {
        RECEIVED,
        PROCESSING,
        PICKING,
        PACKING,
        SHIPPED,
        DELIVERED,
        CANCELED,
        ON_HOLD,
        FAILED
    }

    /**
     * WMS health check result.
     */
    record WmsHealth(
            HealthState state,
            String description,
            Duration responseTime,
            Instant checkedAt
    ) {
        public enum HealthState { OK, DEGRADED, DOWN }
    }

    /**
     * WMS integration metadata.
     */
    record WmsMetadata(
            String vendor,
            String apiVersion,
            String endpointUrl
    ) {}

    /* ========================================================================
     * Exception
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Exception for WMS integration failures.
     */
    class WmsIntegrationException extends RuntimeException {
        private final ErrorCategory category;

        public WmsIntegrationException(String message, ErrorCategory category) {
            super(message);
            this.category = category;
        }

        public WmsIntegrationException(String message, Throwable cause, ErrorCategory category) {
            super(message, cause);
            this.category = category;
        }

        public ErrorCategory category() {
            return category;
        }

        public enum ErrorCategory {
            NETWORK,
            AUTHENTICATION,
            VALIDATION,
            RATE_LIMIT,
            WMS_REJECTION,
            TIMEOUT,
            OTHER
        }
    }
}
```

### 2.2 Inbound Port: `UpdateStockUseCase` (Driving Port)

**Location:** `sprintcart-pro-domain/src/main/java/com/sprintcart/domain/ports/in/inventory/UpdateStockUseCase.java`

This is a **Use Case** port (inbound/driving) that defines the contract for updating stock levels. The application service implements this interface; the WMS adapter's controller calls it.

```java
package com.sprintcart.domain.ports.in.inventory;

import java.time.Instant;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Objects;
import java.util.UUID;

/**
 * Inbound port (Use Case) for handling stock level updates from external systems.
 * <p>
 * This interface is technology-agnostic and must be implemented by an application
 * service. External adapters (REST controllers, message consumers) invoke this
 * port to update inventory levels in the domain.
 *
 * <p><strong>Idempotency:</strong> Implementations must support idempotent operations
 * using the provided {@code correlationId} to prevent duplicate processing.
 */
public interface UpdateStockUseCase {

    /**
     * Processes a batch of stock updates from an external source (e.g., WMS).
     *
     * @param command Contains stock adjustments and metadata.
     * @return Result indicating success/failure for each SKU.
     * @throws InvalidStockUpdateException if validation fails.
     */
    StockUpdateResult updateStock(UpdateStockCommand command)
            throws InvalidStockUpdateException;

    /**
     * Processes a single SKU stock update.
     *
     * @param command Single SKU update details.
     * @return Result for the single update.
     */
    SingleSkuUpdateResult updateSingleSku(SingleSkuUpdateCommand command)
            throws InvalidStockUpdateException;

    /* ========================================================================
     * Command Objects
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Command for batch stock updates.
     */
    record UpdateStockCommand(
            String correlationId,
            String sourceSystem,
            Instant receivedAt,
            List<StockAdjustment> adjustments
    ) {
        public UpdateStockCommand {
            Objects.requireNonNull(correlationId, "correlationId must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(sourceSystem, "sourceSystem must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(adjustments, "adjustments must not be null");
            if (adjustments.isEmpty()) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("adjustments must not be empty");
            }
        }
    }

    /**
     * Command for single SKU update.
     */
    record SingleSkuUpdateCommand(
            String correlationId,
            String sourceSystem,
            String sku,
            int newQuantity,
            String warehouseLocation,
            StockUpdateReason reason,
            Instant effectiveAt
    ) {
        public SingleSkuUpdateCommand {
            Objects.requireNonNull(correlationId, "correlationId must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(sku, "sku must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(reason, "reason must not be null");
            if (newQuantity < 0) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("newQuantity cannot be negative");
            }
        }
    }

    /**
     * Individual stock adjustment within a batch.
     */
    record StockAdjustment(
            String sku,
            int previousQuantity,
            int newQuantity,
            String warehouseLocation,
            StockUpdateReason reason
    ) {
        public StockAdjustment {
            Objects.requireNonNull(sku, "sku must not be null");
            Objects.requireNonNull(reason, "reason must not be null");
            if (newQuantity < 0) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("newQuantity cannot be negative");
            }
        }
    }

    /**
     * Reason for stock adjustment.
     */
    enum StockUpdateReason {
        WMS_SYNC,
        GOODS_RECEIVED,
        RETURN_PROCESSED,
        DAMAGED,
        CYCLE_COUNT,
        SHRINKAGE,
        MANUAL_ADJUSTMENT,
        TRANSFER
    }

    /* ========================================================================
     * Result Objects
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Result of batch stock update.
     */
    record StockUpdateResult(
            String correlationId,
            int totalProcessed,
            int successCount,
            int failureCount,
            List<SkuUpdateStatus> details,
            Instant processedAt
    ) {}

    /**
     * Result for single SKU update.
     */
    record SingleSkuUpdateResult(
            String correlationId,
            String sku,
            boolean success,
            String message,
            int finalQuantity,
            Instant processedAt
    ) {}

    /**
     * Status for individual SKU within batch.
     */
    record SkuUpdateStatus(
            String sku,
            boolean success,
            String errorMessage,
            int finalQuantity
    ) {}

    /* ========================================================================
     * Exceptions
     * ======================================================================== */

    /**
     * Thrown when stock update validation fails.
     */
    class InvalidStockUpdateException extends Exception {
        public InvalidStockUpdateException(String message) {
            super(message);
        }

        public InvalidStockUpdateException(String message, Throwable cause) {
            super(message, cause);
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 3. Adapter Implementation Plan

### 3.1 Package Structure for `wms-adapter`

```
wms-adapter/
└── src/main/java/com/sprintcart/adapters/wms/
    ├── config/
    │   ├── WmsAdapterConfiguration.java    // Spring configuration
    │   ├── WmsSecurityConfiguration.java   // Webhook auth config
    │   └── WmsClientProperties.java        // @ConfigurationProperties
    │
    ├── inbound/                            // Driving adapters (WMS -> SprintCart)
    │   ├── WmsWebhookController.java       // REST endpoint for WMS callbacks
    │   ├── dto/
    │   │   ├── StockUpdateWebhookDto.java
    │   │   └── FulfillmentStatusWebhookDto.java
    │   └── mapper/
    │       └── WmsInboundMapper.java
    │
    ├── outbound/                           // Driven adapters (SprintCart -> WMS)
    │   ├── WmsRestClient.java              // Implements WmsPort
    │   ├── dto/
    │   │   ├── WmsFulfillmentRequestDto.java
    │   │   ├── WmsFulfillmentResponseDto.java
    │   │   └── WmsStatusResponseDto.java
    │   └── mapper/
    │       └── WmsOutboundMapper.java
    │
    └── event/
        └── OrderPlacedEventListener.java   // Subscribes to OrderPlacedEvent
```

### 3.2 Outbound Adapter: `WmsRestClient`

**Location:** `wms-adapter/src/main/java/com/sprintcart/adapters/wms/outbound/WmsRestClient.java`

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Implements `WmsPort` interface from domain
- Uses `WebClient` for non-blocking HTTP calls
- Applies resilience patterns (circuit breaker, retry, timeout)
- Handles authentication (API key, OAuth2, etc.)
- Maps domain objects to/from WMS API DTOs

```java
package com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.outbound;

import com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.config.WmsClientProperties;
import com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.outbound.dto.*;
import com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.outbound.mapper.WmsOutboundMapper;
import com.sprintcart.domain.ports.out.wms.WmsPort;
import io.github.resilience4j.circuitbreaker.annotation.CircuitBreaker;
import io.github.resilience4j.retry.annotation.Retry;
import io.github.resilience4j.timelimiter.annotation.TimeLimiter;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import lombok.extern.slf4j.Slf4j;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import org.springframework.web.reactive.function.client.WebClient;

import java.time.Clock;
import java.time.Duration;
import java.time.Instant;
import java.util.UUID;
import java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture;

/**
 * Outbound adapter implementing {@link WmsPort} for WMS API communication.
 * <p>
 * This adapter is responsible for:
 * <ul>
 *     <li>Translating domain objects to WMS API DTOs</li>
 *     <li>Making HTTP calls to the WMS REST API</li>
 *     <li>Handling errors and applying resilience patterns</li>
 *     <li>Translating WMS responses back to domain objects</li>
 * </ul>
 */
@Slf4j
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class WmsRestClient implements WmsPort {

    private final WebClient wmsWebClient;
    private final WmsClientProperties properties;
    private final WmsOutboundMapper mapper;
    private final Clock clock;

    @Override
    @CircuitBreaker(name = "wms", fallbackMethod = "submitFulfillmentFallback")
    @Retry(name = "wms")
    @TimeLimiter(name = "wms")
    public CompletableFuture<FulfillmentAcknowledgment> submitFulfillmentRequest(
            FulfillmentRequest request) {

        log.info("Submitting fulfillment request to WMS for order {}", request.orderId());

        WmsFulfillmentRequestDto dto = mapper.toWmsRequest(request);

        return wmsWebClient.post()
                .uri("/v1/fulfillment/orders")
                .header("X-Idempotency-Key", request.correlationId())
                .header("X-API-Key", properties.getApiKey())
                .bodyValue(dto)
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(WmsFulfillmentResponseDto.class)
                .map(mapper::toAcknowledgment)
                .doOnSuccess(ack -> log.info("WMS accepted fulfillment for order {}, WMS ref: {}",
                        request.orderId(), ack.wmsReferenceId()))
                .doOnError(ex -> log.error("WMS fulfillment submission failed for order {}",
                        request.orderId(), ex))
                .toFuture();
    }

    // Fallback method for circuit breaker
    private CompletableFuture<FulfillmentAcknowledgment> submitFulfillmentFallback(
            FulfillmentRequest request, Throwable throwable) {

        log.warn("WMS circuit breaker open, returning degraded response for order {}",
                request.orderId());
        throw new WmsIntegrationException(
                "WMS service unavailable",
                throwable,
                WmsIntegrationException.ErrorCategory.NETWORK);
    }

    @Override
    @CircuitBreaker(name = "wms")
    public CompletableFuture<FulfillmentStatusResponse> getFulfillmentStatus(UUID orderId) {
        return wmsWebClient.get()
                .uri("/v1/fulfillment/orders/{orderId}/status", orderId)
                .header("X-API-Key", properties.getApiKey())
                .retrieve()
                .bodyToMono(WmsStatusResponseDto.class)
                .map(mapper::toStatusResponse)
                .toFuture();
    }

    @Override
    @CircuitBreaker(name = "wms")
    public CompletableFuture<Boolean> cancelFulfillment(UUID orderId, String reason) {
        return wmsWebClient.post()
                .uri("/v1/fulfillment/orders/{orderId}/cancel", orderId)
                .header("X-API-Key", properties.getApiKey())
                .bodyValue(new CancelRequestDto(reason))
                .retrieve()
                .toBodilessEntity()
                .map(response -> response.getStatusCode().is2xxSuccessful())
                .toFuture();
    }

    @Override
    public WmsHealth healthCheck() {
        Instant start = clock.instant();
        try {
            Boolean healthy = wmsWebClient.get()
                    .uri("/health")
                    .retrieve()
                    .toBodilessEntity()
                    .map(r -> r.getStatusCode().is2xxSuccessful())
                    .block(Duration.ofSeconds(5));

            return new WmsHealth(
                    Boolean.TRUE.equals(healthy) ? WmsHealth.HealthState.OK : WmsHealth.HealthState.DEGRADED,
                    "WMS API responded",
                    Duration.between(start, clock.instant()),
                    clock.instant()
            );
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return new WmsHealth(
                    WmsHealth.HealthState.DOWN,
                    "WMS API unreachable: " + e.getMessage(),
                    Duration.between(start, clock.instant()),
                    clock.instant()
            );
        }
    }

    @Override
    public WmsMetadata metadata() {
        return new WmsMetadata(
                properties.getVendor(),
                properties.getApiVersion(),
                properties.getBaseUrl()
        );
    }

    // Internal DTO for cancel request
    private record CancelRequestDto(String reason) {}
}
```

### 3.3 Inbound Adapter: `WmsWebhookController`

**Location:** `wms-adapter/src/main/java/com/sprintcart/adapters/wms/inbound/WmsWebhookController.java`

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Exposes REST endpoint(s) for WMS webhook callbacks
- Validates webhook signatures for security
- Maps incoming DTOs to use case commands
- Delegates to application layer (not domain directly)
- Returns appropriate HTTP responses

```java
package com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.inbound;

import com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.inbound.dto.StockUpdateWebhookDto;
import com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.inbound.mapper.WmsInboundMapper;
import com.sprintcart.domain.ports.in.inventory.UpdateStockUseCase;
import com.sprintcart.domain.ports.in.inventory.UpdateStockUseCase.*;
import jakarta.validation.Valid;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import lombok.extern.slf4j.Slf4j;
import org.springframework.http.HttpStatus;
import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;
import org.springframework.validation.annotation.Validated;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;

import java.time.Instant;

/**
 * Inbound adapter (REST controller) that handles WMS webhook callbacks.
 * <p>
 * This controller is deliberately thin - it validates requests, maps DTOs to
 * domain commands, and delegates all business logic to the application layer
 * via the {@link UpdateStockUseCase} port.
 *
 * <h3>Security</h3>
 * Endpoints are secured via HMAC signature validation configured in
 * {@code WmsSecurityConfiguration}. The WMS must sign requests with a
 * shared secret.
 */
@Slf4j
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/wms/webhooks")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Validated
public class WmsWebhookController {

    private final UpdateStockUseCase updateStockUseCase;
    private final WmsInboundMapper mapper;

    /**
     * Endpoint for WMS to push stock level updates.
     * <p>
     * The WMS calls this endpoint whenever inventory levels change
     * (goods received, shipments, cycle counts, etc.).
     *
     * @param signature    HMAC signature from X-WMS-Signature header
     * @param webhookId    Unique webhook event ID for idempotency
     * @param payload      Stock update payload from WMS
     * @return Acknowledgment with processing results
     */
    @PostMapping("/stock-updates")
    public ResponseEntity<StockUpdateResponseDto> handleStockUpdate(
            @RequestHeader(value = "X-WMS-Signature", required = true) String signature,
            @RequestHeader(value = "X-WMS-Webhook-Id", required = true) String webhookId,
            @Valid @RequestBody StockUpdateWebhookDto payload) {

        log.info("Received stock update webhook from WMS. Webhook ID: {}, SKU count: {}",
                webhookId, payload.getAdjustments().size());

        try {
            // Map DTO to domain command
            UpdateStockCommand command = mapper.toCommand(payload, webhookId);

            // Delegate to application layer use case
            StockUpdateResult result = updateStockUseCase.updateStock(command);

            log.info("Stock update processed. Webhook ID: {}, Success: {}/{}, Failures: {}",
                    webhookId, result.successCount(), result.totalProcessed(), result.failureCount());

            return ResponseEntity.ok(new StockUpdateResponseDto(
                    webhookId,
                    result.successCount(),
                    result.failureCount(),
                    result.processedAt()
            ));

        } catch (InvalidStockUpdateException e) {
            log.warn("Invalid stock update from WMS. Webhook ID: {}, Error: {}",
                    webhookId, e.getMessage());
            return ResponseEntity.badRequest()
                    .body(new StockUpdateResponseDto(webhookId, 0, payload.getAdjustments().size(),
                            Instant.now(), e.getMessage()));
        }
    }

    /**
     * Endpoint for WMS to push fulfillment status updates.
     * <p>
     * Called when fulfillment status changes (picked, packed, shipped, etc.).
     */
    @PostMapping("/fulfillment-status")
    public ResponseEntity<Void> handleFulfillmentStatus(
            @RequestHeader(value = "X-WMS-Signature", required = true) String signature,
            @RequestHeader(value = "X-WMS-Webhook-Id", required = true) String webhookId,
            @Valid @RequestBody FulfillmentStatusWebhookDto payload) {

        log.info("Received fulfillment status update from WMS. Order: {}, Status: {}",
                payload.getOrderId(), payload.getStatus());

        // Delegate to appropriate use case for status update handling
        // This would update order status and emit domain events

        return ResponseEntity.accepted().build();
    }

    /**
     * Health check endpoint for WMS to verify connectivity.
     */
    @GetMapping("/health")
    public ResponseEntity<String> healthCheck() {
        return ResponseEntity.ok("OK");
    }

    // Response DTOs

    public record StockUpdateResponseDto(
            String webhookId,
            int successCount,
            int failureCount,
            Instant processedAt,
            String errorMessage
    ) {
        public StockUpdateResponseDto(String webhookId, int successCount, int failureCount, Instant processedAt) {
            this(webhookId, successCount, failureCount, processedAt, null);
        }
    }
}
```

### 3.4 Event Listener: `OrderPlacedEventListener`

**Location:** `wms-adapter/src/main/java/com/sprintcart/adapters/wms/event/OrderPlacedEventListener.java`

This component subscribes to `OrderPlacedEvent` domain events and triggers WMS fulfillment requests.

```java
package com.sprintcart.adapters.wms.event;

import com.sprintcart.application.service.DomainEventProcessor.DomainEvent;
import com.sprintcart.application.service.DomainEventProcessor.DomainEventSubscriber;
import com.sprintcart.domain.events.OrderPlacedEvent;
import com.sprintcart.domain.ports.out.wms.WmsPort;
import com.sprintcart.domain.ports.out.wms.WmsPort.*;
import lombok.NonNull;
import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import lombok.extern.slf4j.Slf4j;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

import java.time.Instant;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

/**
 * Domain event subscriber that listens for {@link OrderPlacedEvent}s and
 * triggers fulfillment requests to the WMS.
 * <p>
 * This follows the event-driven pattern established by the existing
 * {@link com.sprintcart.application.service.DomainEventProcessor}.
 */
@Slf4j
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class OrderPlacedEventListener implements DomainEventSubscriber<OrderPlacedEvent> {

    private final WmsPort wmsPort;

    @Override
    public void handle(@NonNull OrderPlacedEvent event) {
        log.info("Processing OrderPlacedEvent for order {}", event.getOrderId());

        FulfillmentRequest request = mapToFulfillmentRequest(event);

        wmsPort.submitFulfillmentRequest(request)
                .thenAccept(ack -> log.info("WMS acknowledged fulfillment for order {}. WMS Ref: {}",
                        event.getOrderId(), ack.wmsReferenceId()))
                .exceptionally(ex -> {
                    log.error("Failed to submit fulfillment to WMS for order {}",
                            event.getOrderId(), ex);
                    // In production: publish to DLQ or retry queue
                    return null;
                });
    }

    @Override
    public boolean supports(@NonNull Class<? extends DomainEvent> eventType) {
        return OrderPlacedEvent.class.equals(eventType);
    }

    private FulfillmentRequest mapToFulfillmentRequest(OrderPlacedEvent event) {
        var lineItems = event.getOrderLines().stream()
                .map(line -> new FulfillmentLineItem(
                        line.getProductId(),
                        line.getSku(),
                        line.getSku(), // Product name would come from enrichment
                        line.getQuantity(),
                        null
                ))
                .collect(Collectors.toList());

        // ShippingDetails would be fetched from Order aggregate or enriched
        ShippingDetails shippingDetails = new ShippingDetails(
                "Customer Name", // Would come from order/customer service
                "Address Line 1",
                null,
                "City",
                "State",
                "12345",
                "US",
                null,
                "STANDARD"
        );

        return new FulfillmentRequest(
                event.getOrderId(),
                event.getCustomerId(),
                event.getCorrelationId() != null ? event.getCorrelationId() : event.eventId().toString(),
                shippingDetails,
                lineItems,
                FulfillmentPriority.STANDARD,
                Instant.now()
        );
    }
}
```

